<div id="comments" class="comments-area">

			<h2 class="comments-title">
			5 thoughts on &ldquo;Comic&#8217;s Hearing&rdquo;		</h2>

		
		<ol class="comment-list">
					<li id="comment-1192" class="comment byuser comment-author-docinatrix even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-1192" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=112&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo avatar-default' height='56' width='56' />						<b class="fn"><a href='http://extemporanea.livejournal.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>docinatrix</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2011/02/04/comics-hearing/#comment-1192">
							<time datetime="2011-02-08T17:50:51+00:00">
								February 8, 2011 at 5:50 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I loved this, it made me giggle. It&#8217;s a beautiful conflation of the two single-voice situations, and the way you segue between them is cunning and amusing. I particularly enjoyed the gag moments &#8211; &#8220;I meant as drunk as a lord, mi’lord&#8221; (minor nitpick, it&#8217;s more usually spelled &#8220;milord&#8221; or &#8220;m&#8217;lud&#8221;) and &#8220;all lawyers are soulless fucks&#8221;&#8230; you have to simply enjoy the speaker joyously digging himself into a bigger and bigger hole. In a sense the actual crime, while amusing, isn&#8217;t really the point &#8211; the point is the dissolving of boundaries between the two voices. Thank you, my week badly needed this kind of enjoyment.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

